[0.000, "o", "#\u001b[6d\b# The following lines prevent .htaccess and .htpasswd files from being\r\u001b[7d# viewed by Web clients.\r\u001b[8d"]
[0.001, "o", "#\u001b[9d\b<Files \".ht*\">\u001b[K\u001b[11;3HFiles>\u001b[K\u001b[14;3HErrorLog: The location of the error log file.\u001b[K\u001b[15;3HIf you do not specify an ErrorLog directive within a <VirtualHost>\u001b[16;3H"]
[0.000, "o", "container, error messages relating to that virtual host will be\u001b[K\u001b[17;3Hlogged here.  If you *do* define an error logfile for a <VirtualHost>\u001b[18;3Hcontainer, that host's errors will be logged there and not here.\r\u001b[19d#\u001b[K\u001b[20d\b"]
[0.000, "o", "ErrorLog \"/var/log/httpd/error_log\"\r\u001b[21d\u001b[K\u001b[22d#\u001b[K\u001b[23d\b"]
[0.000, "o", "# LogLevel: Control the number of messages logged to the error_log.\r\u001b[24d"]
[0.002, "o", "# Possible values \u001b[30m\u001b[43minclude\u001b[39;49m\u001b[m\u000f: debug, info, notice, warn, error, crit,\u001b[K\r\u001b[25d# alert, emerg.\r\u001b[26d#\u001b[K\u001b[27d\bLogLevel warn\u001b[K\r\u001b[28d\u001b[K\u001b[29d<IfModule log_config_module>\u001b[K\u001b[30;7H\u001b[K\u001b[31dThe following directives define some format nicknames for use with\u001b[32;7Ha CustomLog directive (see below).\u001b[33;5H#\u001b[K\u001b[34d\bLogFormat \"%h %l %u %t \\\"%r\\\" %>s %b \\\"%{Referer}i\\\" \\\"%{User-Agent}i\\\"\" combined\u001b[35;5HLogFormat \"%h %l %u %t \\\"%r\\\" %>s %b\" common\r\u001b[36d\u001b[K\u001b[37;5H<IfModule logio_module>\u001b[K\u001b[38;5H  # You need to enable mod_logio.c to use %I and %O\u001b[39;5H  LogFormat \"%h %l %u %t \\\"%r\\\" %>s %b \\\"%{Referer}i\\\" \\\"%{User-Agent}i\\\" %I %O\" combinedio\u001b[40;5H</IfModule>\u001b[K\u001b[43;7HThe location and format of the access logfile (Common Logfile Format).\u001b[44;7HIf you do not define any access logfiles within a <VirtualHost>\u001b[45;5H# container, they will be logged here.  Contrariwise, if you *do*\u001b[24;19H"]
